snippet.textDisplay: So an opportunity popped up with a really good find, so I went and bought it for $500!!! This really shows you what you can do to find your first project car, find a budget suv, etc with minimal risk and a lot of potential reward!!! We used all common hand tools and did this job at home ourselves! Craftsman was bought by Stanley and now they have decent tools for the price! Worth taking a look at for sure! I messed with the 150 piece set for the first time and I liked it. It got the job done and I think you guys looking for your first set would find it to be a good starter set! Here is the link to the tool sets: http://bit.ly/2PNfHLS

snippet.textDisplay: Hey Chris, you probably don't realize how important your videos are to some people, but I wanna let you know. About 4 years ago I bought my first vehicle, an $800, 1997 Dodge Ram 1500, and it completely changed my life. I was 17 and had pretty much given up on highschool and worked full time flipping burgers. When I bought the truck it needed a lot of work, and with the minimal hand tools I could find at home I used your videos as a bible of automotive repair and the addiction started. I fell in love with the feeling of a having a wrench in my hand and grease on my knuckles. Because of the amazing advice I found in your videos and my desire to learn more I re-enrolled in school, graduated and was accepted into the local tech school for aviation maintenance. Currently I'm employeed as am aviation maintenance technician for the world's largest airline and love every single second of it. I watch every one of your videos, even if it's something I already have done or know how to do. I watch all of them because of the phenomenal production quality and the passion for education, content production and wrenching that is so present in your voice throughout your videos. I'd like to thank you for the amazing content you produce and for changing my life without even knowing it. I hope that youtube is blessed with your knowledge for years to come and that someday you inspire 100 more teenagers like myself.
